Most Beanstalk blocks have a colon at the start and a semicolon at the end.

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    greet |name String|:
        io.line([: Hello, [name]])
    ;
]

The colon opens the function body. The semicolon closes it.

Semicolons do not end every line. Add one only when the surrounding block is
finished.

Use indentation to make nesting easy to see:

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    if ready:
        io.line("Ready!")
    ;
]
